title: England Me GOLD Ke INDIAN Singhasan!
transcript: The British gathered in England during their rule. The Kings of the Kingdom, no matter how much they look, they are swords. What you see behind me is the sword of Orange Zabe. Do you know the sword of Dara Shikho? Yes. The one who was shot and killed. This black sword of Dara Shikho. You see the swords of the warriors of Jodhpur Rajasthan. There are many different swords. Different daggers. But the most significant thing is that of the Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj. The one who was shot by Afzal Khan. It seems easy to hide a small one. This is the lion of Maharaj Ranjit Singh. Which is made of wood. But it is plated with solid gold. And this is his sword. You can see. And on this side, his main sword. On which there are many weapons. Which can be used in a Sikh warrior. It can be very lethal. Like, share, subscribe to support our page. Do follow.

transcript: The sword of 65 kilos is called Yasa ji. The one who fights alone with 2000 soldiers is called Baji. The one who cuts his hand and still fights is called Tana ji. The one who takes the horse from Delhi to Pune in 8 hours is called Santaji. The one who runs away with only 7000 marathas and 30,000 Moghuls is called Ram ji. The one who enters the Moghuls' houses and makes them fools and makes them spy is called Bahir ji. The one who hits the bull on the head of the bull is called Jeevaji. The one who cuts the head of Abjalkhan is called Sambha ji. The one who enters the enemy's houses and hits is called Dhanaji. The one who fights with the lion is called Chhatrapati Sambha ji. And the one who takes all of them together and makes them spy is called Chhatrapati Shivaji.

महाराणा प्रताप और राणा पूंजा भील के बिना मेवाड़ के स्वाभिमान की कल्पना अधूरी है। इतिहास इस बात का प्रमाण देता है कि राजगद्दी के स्तंभ पर आज भी दो महायोद्धाओं की तलवारें अंकित हैं—एक ओर महाराणा प्रताप और दूसरी ओर वीर राणा पूंजा भील।

राणा पूंजा भील को राजपूत की उपाधि देने का प्रयास किया गया, किंतु उन्होंने इसे स्वीकार करने से इनकार कर दिया और अपनी भील पहचान को आदरपूर्वक बनाए रखा। ऐतिहासिक रूप से यह भी कहा जाता है कि महाराणा प्रताप भी इस भूमि के मूल निवासी थे।मूल निवास (जो आदि काल से निवास करता है, अर्थात आदि + वासी = आदिवासी कहा जाता है)।


युद्ध के संकटमय समय में राणा पूंजा भील और उनकी सेना के बिना कोई भी संघर्ष सफल नहीं हो सकता था। जब महाराणा प्रताप को वनवास भोगना पड़ा, तब भील सेना ने उन्हें सुरक्षित रखा और उनके स्वराज्य संघर्ष में अतुलनीय योगदान दिया।
